shared_text:
Breckenridge Area Action Committee
June 23 at 12:51 PM ¬∑

We are looking forward to the 4th of July Celebration next week and have heard from a few people who are equally excited and want to know how they can help support the event. Donations can be made to the Breckenridge Area Action Committee, a promotional committee of the Gratiot Area Chamber of Commerce, and can be dropped off at the Village of Breckenridge offices. All money raised will go to the cost of the fireworks. We also have sponsorship opportunities available for businesses.

Another great way to support the event is to run or walk in the Firecracker 8K that morning. The money goes to support the fireworks that evening, and you get a great tank top for participating: https://runsignup.com/Race/MI/Breckenridge/FirecrackerRunWalk

This year we are expecting a great turnout, and are excited to showcase the businesses and community that make Breckenridge a wonderful place to live and visit! For more information call 989-463-5525.

It is with great disappointment, that we are announcing the official cancellation of the 2020 Breckenridge Little League season. With all of the uncertainty still surrounding the time table of when we would be allowed to play, as well as guidelines we would have to follow, we felt this was the right decision.

We will be beginning the process of refunding sign-up fees in the next week. If you paid through PayPal, your money will be refunded back to your account, please allow 7-10 days for your money to arrive in your account.

If you paid via check or cash, we will be sending reimbursement checks. We need those of you who will be receiving a check to fill out the Google Form on the‚Ä¶

shared_text:
Breckenridge / Wheeler Area Historical Society
May 10 at 6:22 AM ¬∑

Please remember that we are having a perennial plant sale fund raiser this FRIDAY AND SATURDAY (MAY 15 AND 16) from 9 - 1 each day. A partial list of varieties available would be - Allium, sedum, hydrangea, rose of Sharon, rhubarb, brunera, primrose, catmint, hostas, campanula, black-eyed Susans, Canadian and Japanese anemone, coneflowers, European ginger, oriental limelight, flycatchers, yellow sundrops, bee balm, lemon balm, day lilies, and lots of others. Lately when I ride my bike around the section I don't see a single car. Part of the quarantine I figure. The thing I do see is the Breckenridge School Buses out delivering food to many of the families and children in our area. I am so happy this is happening and I think about how excited some of these kids are to see this extra food during this time. I raised 3 kids and I know kids always seem to be hungry. Thank you to all of those that are making this happen and especially to the bus drivers,and those who are helping deliver the food packages. I am so proud of our schools here and I am amazed at all of the great people that live in this community.

A parent wrote this for his local teachers about distance learning. ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

Here is the letter:

Hey teachers, I just wanted to let you know that however this week goes down - it's all good. We're on your team. This wasn't what you signed up for, and I sort of can't believe you're actually going to attempt do this. Your life is about to become one giant conference call with two dozen nine-year-olds who have no set bedtime, and are hopped up on Captain Crunch and whatever their parents have been stress-baking for the past 12 days. What could possibly go wrong?

In light of this, our family is giving you blanket permission to do this however the hell you want for the next two months.

Your kid‚Ä¶

Hello Huskies!
We are with you in spirit and sadness as we process the Governor's EO and are working on a plan for a new normal. We agree that the public health is the primary concern and know that your health and life are more important now more than ever. We love to teach, we love to learn and we love to love. We plan to continue the teaching, the learning and the loving in a different way. We are stronger together in spirit and stronger while physically apart now.

shared_text:
Make
March 14 at 9:16 AM ¬∑

Please share:

Due to school closures, I will be offering free art lessons on our Facebook page each weekday until our kiddos return to school. These will be family oriented for a range of ages and utilize supplies typically found in your home.

Creativity can ease stress, expedite learning & allow us to see circumstances in different ways. Since we will all be home gathered together over the next few weeks unexpectedly, it is the perfect time to discover and grow new talent! We will be offering take home kits from the studio for additional lessons beginning next Wednesday.
I always pull from my classical training as a BFA studio art major and 25 years as a professional artist, but also love to introduce process learning- In other words- I like to show you how to do it AND get messy!

Join us at 1pm CT this Monday for our first lesson!
Hint: For Monday, gather plain paper, a baking sheet, cooking spray/oil and pencils...we will be drawing faces!

First off, we would like to give a special thank you to all of our past and present members, our fantastic alumni and all of our amazing supporters! We appreciate you all very deeply! Secondly, we are holding dress up days so our members can show their pride to FFA.
Monday- Boots Day
Tuesday- Hat Day (give 50 cents to Ms. Fishburn)
Wednesday- Ice Cream at lunch
Thursday- Country Day
Friday- FFA Shirt Day
Everyone have a great weekend and be ready for dress up days!
